      "content": "Scholars who support originalism often argue that this philosophy is not inherently conservative, but rather a method to ensure the Constitution remains a stable and consistent document. They counter the conservative agenda claim by emphasizing that originalism seeks to limit judicial activism and prevent judges from imposing their personal beliefs. Instead, it focuses on the text and historical context, which they argue is a fairer and more objective approach to constitutional interpretation. They also note that originalism can appeal to judges of all political persuasions, as it emphasizes impartiality and adherence to the framers' intent rather than contemporary political ideologies.",
